{{Poland-bio-stub}}

The '''Kierkegaard Circle''' at [[Trinity College, Toronto|Trinity College]], [[University of Toronto]], is a [[philosophy|philosophical]] [[learned society|society]] founded in 1986 whose purpose is to promote the study of the philosophy and theology of [[Søren Kierkegaard]] in [[Canada]].<ref name="Stewart">{{cite journal|last=Stewart|first=Jon|date=January 2009|title=Kierkegaard's International Reception – The Near East, Asia, Australia and the Americas|location=University of Copenhagen, Denmark|volume=3|issue=8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sMffGQKgJ9EC&pg=PA211&dq=%22Kierkegaard+Circle%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=AXsJUZG4G4u70AGzhIHgDg&ved=0CC4Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22Kierkegaard%20Circle%22&f=false}}</ref>
